==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swaddling
<hw>Swad"dling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Swaddle</er>, <pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Swaddling band</b></col>, <col><b>Swaddling
cloth</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Swaddling clout</b></col></mcol>,
<cd>a band or cloth wrapped round an infant, especially round a newborn
infant.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye shall find the babe wrapped in <qex>swaddling clothes</qex>,
lying in a manger.</q> <rj><qau>Luke ii. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swag</ent>⟦br⟧
